        <div class="nomination clearfix list has-custom has-showhide" id="nomination-31c981bd-49a6-4350-879f-45c96e60aeda" data-slug="49a6-editorial-team-of-the-year" data-winnerclass="Highly Commended" style="display: none">

        <div class="col-xs-12">
            
    
    <div class="winner-badge pull-right ">
        
        Highly Commended
        
    </div>
    
    <div class="nomination-name-container winner-highlight">

        <h4 class="nomination-name"><a href="?nomination=49a6-editorial-team-of-the-year">Editorial Team of the Year</a></h4>
    </div>
    <div class="nomination-info">
                

                
    
    
    
    <div class="nomination-qa Textbox doc">
        <div class="nomination-qu">Company or team name</div>
        
        
        <div class="nomination-an">BBC Shared Data Unit</div>
        


        

    </div>
    

                
                

                
    
    
    
    <div class="nomination-qa TextareaLimit doc">
        <div class="nomination-qu">Executive summary</div>
        
        
        <div class="nomination-an">The BBC Shared Data Unit has continued to promote and support data journalism at a regional level across the UK, whilst making national and local headlines with a series of public interest data investigations.  

The team’s collaborative model sees it share its data journalism with more than 1,000 local news outlets across television, radio, print and digital.   At the same time, its investigations have been widely used across the BBC's flagship news programmes.
 
As well as producing content, the team organised the Data Journalism UK conference in May, in partnership with Birmingham City University.  More than 100 data journalists and students came together to network and explore new ideas in what was one of the first large-scale journalism gatherings in the UK since the pandemic.

We also continue to run free online training sessions for local journalists, including week-long masterclasses in data journalism, our first ever coding course for journalists, as well as hosting drop-in sessions for journalists wanting to learn key technical skills over their lunch-break. 

A commitment to transparency and the open data movement is at the heart of our team and our output.  We have demonstrated how adopting open data principles enhances the trust in our reporting, builds a personal relationship with audiences and helps to engage them in the process of journalism.   We demonstrate our commitment to transparency through sharing source data, methods and code for the majority of the projects we embark upon.
</div>
        


        

    </div>
    

                
                

                
    
    
    
